legs.origNarrative: Go east on Lee Hwy/US-29 N.

maneuvers.narrative: Start out going west on 15th St toward Clarendon Blvd.
15th St becomes N Veitch St.
Turn right onto Lee Hwy/US-29 N.
Turn left onto N Lynn St/US-29 N.
Turn slight left to take the George Washington Memorial Pkwy N ramp.
Stay straight to go onto ramp.
Merge onto George Washington Memorial Parkway/George Washington Memorial Pkwy.
Merge onto Capital Beltway/I-495 N toward Maryland (Crossing into Maryland).
Merge onto I-270 Spur N via EXIT 38 on the left toward Rockville/Frederick.
I-270 Spur N becomes I-270 N.
Keep left to take I-270 (EXPRESS) N.
I-270 (EXPRESS) N becomes I-270 N.
Merge onto I-70 W via EXIT 32 toward Hagerstown (Crossing into Pennsylvania).
Take the US-30 E/I-70 W exit toward New Stanton/Harrisburg/McConnellsburg.
Turn slight right onto Lincoln Hwy/I-70 W/US-30 E.
Merge onto I-70 W toward New Stanton/Harrisburg/Pittsburgh/Pennsylvania Tpke/I-76 (Portions toll).
Merge onto I-76 W toward Pittsburgh (Portions toll) (Crossing into Ohio).
Take Ohio Turnpike toward I-80 W/Cleveland (Portions toll).
Ohio Turnpike becomes I-80 W (Portions toll) (Crossing into Indiana).
Merge onto I-80 W/I-94 W via EXIT 21 toward IN-51 S (Crossing into Illinois).
Keep left to take I-80 W/I-294 N toward Wisconsin-Iowa (Portions toll).
Take the I-80 W exit toward Iowa.
Merge onto I-80 W (Portions toll).
Stay straight to go onto I-280 W (Crossing into Iowa).
Merge onto I-80 W via the exit on the left toward Des Moines (Passing through Nebraska, Wyoming, Utah and Nevada, then crossing into California).
Merge onto I-5 S/CA-99 S/CA-16 E via EXIT 86 toward Los Angeles.
Merge onto J St via EXIT 519B toward Downtown.
Welcome to SACRAMENTO, CA.
